Laura Constance Netzel (née Pistolekors; 1 March 1839 — 10 February 1927) was a Finnish-born Swedish composer, pianist, conductor and concert organizer who sometimes used the pseudonym N. Lago.
In 1866 she married professor Wilhelm Netzel of the Karolinska Institute.
In August 2021 they organized a Laura Netzel Music Festical in Rantasalmi where her songs, instrumental pieces and orchestral works were performed in a series of concerts.
The piano concerto was premiered at Mikkeli Music Festival in 2020.
She was born in Rantasalmi, Finland, and was proud of her Finnish heritage throughout her life, even though she was just one year old when she moved permanently to Stockholm.
